  "prompt": "IRMA ANAND cutoff?",
  "response": "The cutoff for **IRMA Anand** (Institute of Rural Management Anand) varies each year based on factors such as the number of applicants, their performance in the entrance exam, and seat availability. \n\nFor the **IRMA Admission Process**, candidates must appear for the **IRMA Admission Test (IRMA-AT)** or have a valid **CAT/XAT score**. The cutoff percentile for IRMA-AT or CAT/XAT typically ranges between **85-95 percentile** for general category candidates. However, the exact cutoff may differ for reserved categories.\n\nFor example:  \n- **General Category**: 90+ percentile  \n- **OBC/SC/ST Categories**: Slightly lower percentile  \n\nAfter clearing the cutoff, candidates are shortlisted for the **Group Activity (GA)** and **Personal Interview (PI)** rounds. Final selection is based on the overall performance, including test scores, GA, PI, and academic profile.\n\nFor the **most accurate and updated cutoff information**, refer to the **official IRMA website** or the admission brochure for the specific year you are applying for.",
